1
00:00:00,740 --> 00:00:06,220
One of the best ways to consistently make
money trading is to understand the facts and

2
00:00:06,220 --> 00:00:08,149
nuances about the market structure.

3
00:00:08,149 --> 00:00:13,379
Today we’ll cover an important pattern,
the “over and under” break of structure

4
00:00:13,379 --> 00:00:14,490
pattern.

5
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:20,630
So if you could, like, subscribe to the channel
and stick around for the full video.

6
00:00:20,630 --> 00:00:25,130
What is a break of structure?

7
00:00:25,130 --> 00:00:29,779
Market structure is simply the support and
resistance levels on your charts, determined

8
00:00:29,779 --> 00:00:31,869
by swing highs and lows.

9
00:00:31,869 --> 00:00:35,630
These are levels on your chart that attract
the most attention.

10
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:39,910
When the market is in a bullish trend and
buyers are controlling the market, you will

11
00:00:39,910 --> 00:00:42,430
see higher highs and higher lows.

12
00:00:42,430 --> 00:00:44,270
There is strong buying pressure.

13
00:00:44,270 --> 00:00:48,210
This results in the upward movement of price
with time.

14
00:00:48,210 --> 00:00:53,750
The formation of consecutive lower lows and
lower highs in the price is referred a bearish

15
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:54,750
trend.

16
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:57,300
This indicates strong selling pressure.

17
00:00:57,300 --> 00:01:01,110
This results in a downward movement of price
with time.

18
00:01:01,110 --> 00:01:07,060
Now, the over and under pattern represents
a break of structure in the market.

19
00:01:07,060 --> 00:01:11,320
The break of structure is the first sign that
the market is telling you that it's about

20
00:01:11,320 --> 00:01:14,009
to get weaker or it's about to reverse.

21
00:01:14,009 --> 00:01:16,060
Let’s say we have an uptrend.

22
00:01:16,060 --> 00:01:17,920
Higher highs and higher lows.

23
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:23,490
We have a break of the structure when the
price makes a new lower low and lower high.

24
00:01:23,490 --> 00:01:28,070
This tells you that this trend could be weakening
or it could reverse.

25
00:01:28,070 --> 00:01:30,679
For a downtrend, the same concept.

26
00:01:30,679 --> 00:01:32,810
Lower Lows and lower highs.

27
00:01:32,810 --> 00:01:37,439
We have a break of the structure when the
price makes a new higher high and a higher

28
00:01:37,439 --> 00:01:38,439
low.

29
00:01:38,439 --> 00:01:43,600
There's no guarantee that the trend is over,
but this is a warning sign, a sign of weakness

30
00:01:43,600 --> 00:01:45,450
in the previous downtrend.

31
00:01:45,450 --> 00:01:50,670
The over and under pattern

32
00:01:50,670 --> 00:01:55,509
We can distinguish two types of patterns:
• Bullish break of structure, which appears

33
00:01:55,509 --> 00:01:57,940
at the end of a downtrend.

34
00:01:57,940 --> 00:02:02,030
• Bearish break of structure, which appears
at the end of an uptrend.

35
00:02:02,030 --> 00:02:09,080
Here’s how to easily find a bullish over
and under pattern, after a previous downtrend.

36
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:12,610
• Price creates a lower low
• Price creates a lower high

37
00:02:12,610 --> 00:02:17,251
• Price breaches the previous low and creates
a new lower low

38
00:02:17,251 --> 00:02:22,910
• Then price breaks the previous high as
well and forms a higher high

39
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:28,330
When price returns to the zone created by
the 2 previous lows, you look to enter into

40
00:02:28,330 --> 00:02:30,390
a long position.

41
00:02:30,390 --> 00:02:35,010
For a bearish over and under pattern, after
a previous uptrend.

42
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:38,670
• Price creates a higher high
• Price creates a lower high

43
00:02:38,670 --> 00:02:43,031
• Price breaches the previous high and creates
a new higher high

44
00:02:43,031 --> 00:02:48,920
• Then price breaks the previous low as
well and forms a lower low

45
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:53,860
When price returns to the zone created by
the 2 previous highs, you look to enter into

46
00:02:53,860 --> 00:02:55,540
a short position.

47
00:02:55,540 --> 00:03:01,590
Now, you might be inclined to believe that
this break of structure pattern looks similar

48
00:03:01,590 --> 00:03:03,820
to the Head and Shoulder pattern.

49
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:08,900
The main difference between the over and under
pattern and the Head and Shoulder pattern

50
00:03:08,900 --> 00:03:14,310
is the left leg (second valley) of the over
and under formation, which is much lower than

51
00:03:14,310 --> 00:03:15,730
the right leg (first valley).

52
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:20,820
And this is a more common pattern than the
classic head and shoulders, because it involves

53
00:03:20,820 --> 00:03:25,430
2 traps set by the smart money, for both sides.

54
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:30,960
The second major difference between the two
reversal patterns is the entry point.

55
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:37,710
Usually, the point of entry for the HS pattern
is the break of the neckline, but with the

56
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:44,120
over and under pattern, we look for a much
earlier entry near the left wave, which offers

57
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,870
a bigger profit potential.

58
00:03:45,870 --> 00:03:48,250
We’ll talk about this later.

59
00:03:48,250 --> 00:03:53,520
Break of structure & liquidity hunt

60
00:03:53,520 --> 00:03:57,230
So why is this break of structure pattern
important?

61
00:03:57,230 --> 00:04:03,640
For big institutions with a need to fill large
orders, finding pockets of liquidity is absolutely

62
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:05,010
essential.

63
00:04:05,010 --> 00:04:09,930
When these big players take positions in the
market, they obviously aim to be filed at

64
00:04:09,930 --> 00:04:11,930
the best possible price.

65
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:17,340
However, given the size of their positions,
they need to find enough counter-forces to

66
00:04:17,340 --> 00:04:21,539
fill their orders, with the minimal amount
of slippage.

67
00:04:21,539 --> 00:04:27,121
If a big player were to enter the market at
an area of low liquidity, the volatility it

68
00:04:27,121 --> 00:04:32,300
would create would have a negative impact
on the average price it gets.

69
00:04:32,300 --> 00:04:38,080
Lower liquidity usually results in a more
volatile market and will cause prices to change

70
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:39,080
drastically.

71
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,660
So, where do we find these levels?

72
00:04:41,660 --> 00:04:44,050
Where stop-loss orders are placed.

73
00:04:44,050 --> 00:04:47,199
Where do you think the concept of “stop-loss
hunt” comes from?

74
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:52,449
From the necessity that large players have
to enter the market in areas of liquidity

75
00:04:52,449 --> 00:04:55,669
as they aim to accumulate major positions.

76
00:04:55,669 --> 00:05:01,960
These areas will always attract interest because
that’s where pockets of liquidity exist.

77
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:08,449
Now very important: the creation of a liquidity
level comes as a result of an initial imbalance

78
00:05:08,449 --> 00:05:13,849
of supply/demand, which forms what we know
as a swing high or swing low.

79
00:05:13,849 --> 00:05:19,169
As more players take positions in the market,
these are levels where market participants

80
00:05:19,169 --> 00:05:23,610
will use as a historical reference to place
their stops.

81
00:05:23,610 --> 00:05:29,409
In a bearish over and under pattern, the highest
high in the formation, represents the liquidity

82
00:05:29,409 --> 00:05:30,419
hunt.

83
00:05:30,419 --> 00:05:35,259
Lot of traders had their stops places above
the previous swing high.

84
00:05:35,259 --> 00:05:40,819
Smart money pushed the price above the previous
high, grabbed the liquidity and moved price

85
00:05:40,819 --> 00:05:41,830
back down.

86
00:05:41,830 --> 00:05:46,939
I always like to see a clear rejection that
leads to a structure breakout.

87
00:05:46,939 --> 00:05:49,840
And not only the previous higher high was
broken.

88
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:53,759
We also have a breakout of the previous lower
high.

89
00:05:53,759 --> 00:05:58,900
Another liquidity hunt, because the price
is then moved upward, toward the previous

90
00:05:58,900 --> 00:06:00,120
higher high.

91
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:06,220
As a retail trader, it’s very hard to make
money in this context, if you don’t know

92
00:06:06,220 --> 00:06:09,020
what you are doing.

93
00:06:09,020 --> 00:06:13,120
How to trade the break of structure setup
The best time to trade the break of structure

94
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:19,569
pattern is after a significant rally or sell-off
no matter the time frame used (you can use

95
00:06:19,569 --> 00:06:23,270
this on the daily chart down to the 1-minute
chart).

96
00:06:23,270 --> 00:06:27,370
Here are the rules for a short signal, during
a bearish break of structure.

97
00:06:27,370 --> 00:06:36,800
• A prevailing uptrend needs to be visible
– series of HH followed by a series of HL.

98
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:40,829
• Break in the market structure – price
starts to make a lower low LL.

99
00:06:40,829 --> 00:06:45,029
• You plan to enter at the zone between
the right wave and the highest high

100
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:50,330
• You place the protective stop-loss above
the last higher high HH.

101
00:06:50,330 --> 00:06:55,099
• Take profit near the first valley, at
the low of the first down leg.

102
00:06:55,099 --> 00:06:59,580
And the second target at the area of the lower
low.

103
00:06:59,580 --> 00:07:03,580
For a bullish break of structure, meaning
for buy signals:

104
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:11,780
• A prevailing downtrend needs to be visible
– series of LL followed by a series of LH.

105
00:07:11,780 --> 00:07:16,150
• Break in the market structure – price
starts to make a higher high HH.

106
00:07:16,150 --> 00:07:20,299
• You plan to enter at the zone between
the right wave and the lowest low

107
00:07:20,299 --> 00:07:25,449
• You place the protective stop-loss below
the last lower low LL.

108
00:07:25,449 --> 00:07:28,749
• Take profit near the first peak of the
pattern.

109
00:07:28,749 --> 00:07:31,561
And the second target at the area of the higher
high

110
00:07:31,561 --> 00:07:37,639
Break of structure & supply and demand strategy

111
00:07:37,639 --> 00:07:40,779
The break of structure don’t always result
in a reversal.

112
00:07:40,779 --> 00:07:46,119
That’s why you need to find other confluence
factors, to increase the odds in your favor.

113
00:07:46,119 --> 00:07:51,289
Because, with this pattern, I’m basically
trying to align my positions with the smart

114
00:07:51,289 --> 00:07:56,909
money, using supply and demand zones is a
great way to find entry locations.

115
00:07:56,909 --> 00:08:02,099
So the plan is to find the break of structure
pattern, we’ll wait for a retracement back

116
00:08:02,099 --> 00:08:08,090
to the first wave, and we’ll try to find
a supply or demand zone for an entry, to execute

117
00:08:08,090 --> 00:08:10,860
the trade with a greater accuracy.

118
00:08:10,860 --> 00:08:14,199
Here, a significant drop has occurred.

119
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:18,630
The market makes an obvious low, followed
by a lower high.

120
00:08:18,630 --> 00:08:24,199
Then after making a lower low, it shoots up
and breaches the previous high, to make a

121
00:08:24,199 --> 00:08:25,830
higher high.

122
00:08:25,830 --> 00:08:31,050
The space between this low and the second
low is considered as a strong demand zone

123
00:08:31,050 --> 00:08:32,210
itself.

124
00:08:32,210 --> 00:08:34,659
But what if you want even more accuracy.

125
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:39,610
What if you are seeing the pattern on the
Hourly chart and you want to time your entry

126
00:08:39,610 --> 00:08:43,589
on the 15 min time frame or on the 5 min time
frame?

127
00:08:43,589 --> 00:08:46,750
You need to find a demand zone for an entry.

128
00:08:46,750 --> 00:08:51,820
First, you need to take a look at the left-hand
side of previous low, where the strong rally

129
00:08:51,820 --> 00:08:52,820
has started.

130
00:08:52,820 --> 00:08:58,360
Now you need to find out the origin or the
start point of that strong rally.

131
00:08:58,360 --> 00:09:03,790
Remember that demand zones are found when
the market makes a large move up from a single

132
00:09:03,790 --> 00:09:06,350
candle or from a base.

133
00:09:06,350 --> 00:09:12,110
You always draw the demand zone from the last
BEARISH candle before the up move.

134
00:09:12,110 --> 00:09:17,540
When price returns to the zone, you can open
a buy position, with stops below the lowest

135
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:18,540
low.

136
00:09:18,540 --> 00:09:20,180
Here’s our first target.

137
00:09:20,180 --> 00:09:23,029
And here’s our second target.

138
00:09:23,029 --> 00:09:28,100
Of course, anticipating a much bigger break
of structure, you can leave a portion of the

139
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:32,029
trade open, in the case the reversal is much
more aggressive.

140
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:36,520
Here’s another break of structure pattern,
a bearish one.

141
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:42,940
The price is forming a new high level, declines,
then forms a temporary low.

142
00:09:42,940 --> 00:09:48,410
Prices then rally again to exceed the previous
high (making a higher high).

143
00:09:48,410 --> 00:09:52,370
The price then falls to form a new lower low.

144
00:09:52,370 --> 00:09:57,240
This is our first sign that we might have
an over and under pattern.

145
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:03,000
Prices rise again to the initial high level,
so we need to find a supply area.

146
00:10:03,000 --> 00:10:08,930
You look at the left side of the previous
high where the previous strong down move started.

147
00:10:08,930 --> 00:10:13,459
After that, you need to find out the origin
of the strong down move.

148
00:10:13,459 --> 00:10:19,160
Remember, supply zones are found when the
market makes a large down move from a single

149
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,709
candle or from a base.

150
00:10:21,709 --> 00:10:26,709
You draw the supply zone from the last BULLISH
candle before the down move.

151
00:10:26,709 --> 00:10:30,769
This is price area that could represent the
entry trigger.

152
00:10:30,769 --> 00:10:36,699
Stop level can be placed above this higher
high, while partial profits can be taken at

153
00:10:36,699 --> 00:10:47,160
this low and at this low.

154
00:10:47,160 --> 00:11:30,139
Over and under divergence strategy

155
00:11:30,139 --> 00:11:35,980
Another effective way to trade the break of
structure is by using indicators, more specifically

156
00:11:35,980 --> 00:11:40,350
to find divergences between an indicator and
the price.

157
00:11:40,350 --> 00:11:45,620
If that coincides with a supply or demand
zone, it gives you even a better indication

158
00:11:45,620 --> 00:11:48,449
of which way the price will go.

159
00:11:48,449 --> 00:11:53,380
Divergence is when the direction of a technical
indicator, usually some form of oscillator,

160
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:59,870
MACD, RSI, Stochastic, ‘diverges’ from
the overall price trend.

161
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:05,079
In other words, the indicator starts moving
in the opposite direction to the price and

162
00:12:05,079 --> 00:12:10,050
the trading oscillator signals a possible
trend reversal.

163
00:12:10,050 --> 00:12:14,899
Coupled with the initial break of structure,
you have 2 indications that something will

164
00:12:14,899 --> 00:12:16,620
happen in the market.

165
00:12:16,620 --> 00:12:23,490
Bullish divergence is when the price is moving
lower but the indicator turns and points up.

166
00:12:23,490 --> 00:12:29,410
Bearish divergence is when the price is moving
higher but the indicator points down.

167
00:12:29,410 --> 00:12:34,340
The logic behind divergence to analyze the
market is that the indicator is showing a

168
00:12:34,340 --> 00:12:36,759
slowdown in price momentum.

169
00:12:36,759 --> 00:12:40,240
Price momentum will often change before the
price itself.

170
00:12:40,240 --> 00:12:41,910
That’s a leading signal.

171
00:12:41,910 --> 00:12:48,639
So the plan is to find a break of structure,
we wait for the price to return, to trap new

172
00:12:48,639 --> 00:12:54,320
traders, and we want to find a divergence
at the third wave in the structure.

173
00:12:54,320 --> 00:13:00,129
Here’s a bearish break of structure with
a Stochastic divergence confirmation.

174
00:13:00,129 --> 00:13:04,600
Price makes a new high, declines and makes
a new low.

175
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:09,850
Price then rallies above the previous high
to mark a new higher high.

176
00:13:09,850 --> 00:13:14,339
Price then falls quite aggressively to form
a new lower low.

177
00:13:14,339 --> 00:13:16,649
This is our break of structure.

178
00:13:16,649 --> 00:13:21,970
Price then rises towards the initial high,
but does not make a new higher high.

179
00:13:21,970 --> 00:13:27,120
And during this up move, after the break of
structure, we have a bearish divergence on

180
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:28,759
the Stochastic.

181
00:13:28,759 --> 00:13:35,420
This bearish divergence signifies a potential
down move, because prices rally to a new high

182
00:13:35,420 --> 00:13:38,959
while the oscillator refuses to reach a new
level.

183
00:13:38,959 --> 00:13:43,390
In this situation, bulls are losing their
grip on the market.

184
00:13:43,390 --> 00:13:49,860
So a sell entry here is a high probability
trade, with an excellent risk to reward ratio.

185
00:13:49,860 --> 00:13:53,670
The protective stop-loss above the last higher
high HH.

186
00:13:53,670 --> 00:14:45,380
And take profit near the first valley and
the second target at this low.

187
